column1: # SOURCE: Derived from daily_weather_openfield-research.csv and pv_microclimate_factors-research.csv
# DESCRIPTION: Daily weather under agri-PV panels (spatial average at crop level). Open-field weather adjusted by microclimate factors for density_variant=medium (GCR=50%).

# LOGIC: temp_new = temp_openfield + temp_adjustment_c (-1.50C); solar_new = solar_openfield * irradiance_multiplier (0.50); wind_new = wind_openfield * wind_speed_multiplier (0.85). Precipitation passed through unchanged (no panel interception in factors).
# ASSUMPTIONS: Microclimate factors represent spatial average across planted area. Panel height 3m
column2: fixed-tilt 28deg. Values from peer-reviewed agri-PV studies.
